comments: Collins (SAS) moves somewhat forward towards Allen's (CLE) lower body and marginal contact occurs during the shot attempt.
Allen (CLE) is turning away from Jones (SAS) when marginal contact occurs on the perimeter.
Langford (SAS) is already in Mitchell's (CLE) path and is firming up over his left leg when contact occurs.
Jones (SAS) extends his arm into Garland's (CLE) upper body and drives him into Allen (CLE), who subsequently makes contact with Garland's head.
Garland (CLE) brings his hand forward towards Jones (SAS) and marginal contact occurs in the backcourt.
Collins (SAS) is turning away from Garland's (CLE) path as they come together following the pick, and Collins absorbs the marginal contact.
Mobley (CLE) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Jones' (SAS) driving shot attempt.
Collins (SAS) cleanly deflects the ball away from Allen (CLE) during rebounding.
Garland (CLE) releases the ball to pass prior to his foot landing out of bounds.
Collins (SAS) brings his forearm towards Mobley (CLE) and marginal contact occurs as Mobley receives the pass.
Mitchell (CLE) cleanly dislodges the ball from Johnson (SAS) during rebounding.  Any ensuing head contact after the dislodge is marginal.
After the ball is dislodged, Johnson (SAS) flails his arm and makes contact with Mitchell's (CLE) head that affects his ability to secure the loose ball.
Collins (SAS) and LeVert (CLE) cleanly tie each other up, and a jump ball is correctly called.

Replay review of the out of bounds called on Mitchell (CLE) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful.  Richardson (SAS) is the last player to touch the ball and possession is awarded to Cleveland.
Richardson (SAS) cleanly deflects the ball away from Mitchell (CLE) on the perimeter.
Collins (SAS) does not maintain verticality and makes contact with Mitchell's (CLE) arm as he defends the shot near the rim.
Collins (SAS) turns into LeVert (CLE) and delivers contact as he sets the screen.
Collins (SAS) brings his arm down and makes contact with Mobley's (CLE) arm that affects his shot near the rim.
Garland (CLE) brings his hand towards Jones (SAS) and marginal contact occurs as Jones is gathering the ball.
Allen (CLE) jumps alongside Jones' (SAS) path and legally contests the driving shot attempt.
Johnson (SAS) cleanly blocks Mitchell's (CLE) shot attempt before the ball has reaches its apex.
Johnson (SAS) is firming up over his right foot and absorbs the marginal contact from Mitchell (CLE).
